-- JPMorgan: Bear Stearns well run with good risk controls
-- 
-- Mon Mar 17, 2008 12:39am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/17/us-bearstearns-jpmorgan-call-idUSNWEN452120080317

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - JPMorgan Chase said on Sunday that it found Bear Stearns Inc. a well run bank with good risk control. 

 A JPMorgan executive said on a conference call that 200 employees scrutinized Bear Stearn's books over three days. JPMorgan announced earlier it would buy Bear Stearns for about $2 a share. (Reporting by  Joseph Giannone  and  Megan Davies ; Editing by  Tomasz Janowski )